&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="income-hours-featured" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/income-hours-featured-750x448.png" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/income-hours-featured-1090x651.png" /></a></p><p>截至 2021 年美国社区调查，约 15% 的美国工薪阶层每年收入至少为 10 万美元。正如您所预料的那样，许多属于这 15% 的人在学校度过了更长的时间，并在工作中花费了更多的时间。</p><p>但你也可以在不一直工作的情况下赚取六位数的收入。那些人呢？他们在做什么？</p><p><strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/2023/11/20/jobs-with-higher-income-and-fewer-hours/">阅读更多</a></strong></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 72699</post-id></item><item><title>构建公平算法</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2023/11/17/building-fair-algorithms/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Fri, 17 Nov 2023 08:41:20 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Statistics]]></category><category><![CDATA[algorithm]]></category><category><![CDATA[bias]]></category><category><![CDATA[Coursera]]></category><category><![CDATA[Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=72675 </guid><description><![CDATA[Emma Pierson and Kowe Kadoma, for Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center, have a short&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/algorithm/" rel="tag">算法</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/bias/" rel="tag">偏差</a>, <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/coursera/" rel="tag">Coursera</a> , <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/fred-hutchinson-cancer-center/" rel="tag">Fred Hutchinson 癌症中心</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> Fred Hutchinson 癌症中心的 Emma Pierson 和 Kowe Kadoma 在 Coursera 上开设了一门简短的免费课程，<a href="https://www.coursera.org/learn/algorithmic-fairness/">介绍构建公平算法的实际步骤</a>：</p><blockquote><p>算法越来越多地帮助医疗保健、刑事司法、招聘和其他重要领域做出高风险决策。这使得这些算法必须公平，但近年来的情况表明，算法可能会因年龄、性别、国籍、种族和其他属性而产生偏见。本课程将教您设计公平算法的十项实用原则。它将通过现代算法案例研究的具体要点来强调现实世界的相关性，包括刑事司法、医疗保健和 ChatGPT 等大型语言模型中的案例研究。您将了解在尝试设计公平算法并评估算法的公平性时应遵循的基本规则。</p></blockquote><p>它适合初学者，不需要编码。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/algorithm/" rel="tag">算法</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/bias/" rel="tag">偏差</a>, <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/coursera/" rel="tag">Coursera</a> , <a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/fred-hutchinson-cancer-center/" rel="tag">Fred Hutchinson 癌症中心</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 72675</post-id></item><item><title> ✚ 空间有限时的图表选项</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2023/11/16/process-265-little/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Thu, 16 Nov 2023 19:30:50 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[The Process]]></category><category><![CDATA[mobile]]></category><category><![CDATA[options]]></category><category><![CDATA[responsive design]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=72690 </guid><description><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2023/11/16/process-265-little/"><img width="750" height="448" src="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/little-space-featured-750x448.png" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/little-space-featured-750x448.png 750w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/little-space-featured-1090x651.png 1090w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/little-space-featured-210x125.png 210w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/little-space-featured-768x459.png 768w, https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/little-